<paragraph id="AB7DF542464D170CFF17FC1C5A7646E1" blockId="7.[151,1437,1013,1387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFE9DFC1C5AB24618" box="[285,409,1013,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFE9DFC1C5AB24618" box="[285,409,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mainly distributed through the Oriental Region and contains 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFB23FC1C5FEA4619" box="[1187,1217,1013,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="37.0">37</number>
species (
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFAB1FC1C5BCF4620" author="Boulard" pageId="7" pageNumber="17" refString="Boulard, M. (2005 b) Donnees statutaires et ethologiques sur des cigales thailandaises, incluant la description de huit especes nouvelles, ou mal connues. Ecole Pratique des Hautes Etudes, Travaux du Laboratoire Biologie et Evolution des Insectes Hemipteroidea, 15, 5 - 57." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="b">
Boulard, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFF17FBF55BFE4620" box="[151,213,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2005.0">2005</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFF70FBF55AEB4620" author="Chou" box="[240,448,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="17" refString="Chou, I., Lei, Z., Li, L., Lu, X. &amp; Yao, W. (1997) The Cicadidae of China (Homoptera: Cicadoidea). Ilustrataj Insectfaunoj, 2. Tianze Eldoneio, Hong Kong, 380 pp., 16 pls. (In Chinese with English summary)." type="book" year="1997">
Chou 
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFEB7FBF55A584623" box="[311,371,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFE02FBF55AEB4620" box="[386,448,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Duffels and van der 
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFD3DFBF5586E4620" author="Laan" box="[701,837,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; Van der Laan, P. A. (1985) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica, 34. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrecht, xiv + 414 pp." type="book chapter" year="1985">
Laan, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFC87FBF5586E4620" box="[775,837,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFCD2FBF55F2C4620" author="Metcalf" box="[850,1031,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 b) General catalogue of the Homoptera, fascicle VIII, Cicadoidea, part 1. Cicadidae. section II. Gaeninae and Cicadinae. North Carolina State College, Raleigh, pp. 587 - 919." type="journal article" year="1963" yearSuffix="b">
Metcalf, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFC3CFBF558D24620" box="[956,1017,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1963.0">1963</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFB94FBF55E234620" author="Sanborn" box="[1044,1288,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="19" refString="Sanborn, A. F., Phillips, P. K. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) Biodiversity, biogeography, and bibliography of the cicadas of Thailand (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea: Cicadidae). Zootaxa, 1413, 1 - 46." type="journal article" year="2007">
Sanborn 
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFBFEFBF55F924623" box="[1150,1209,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFB48FBF55E234620" box="[1224,1288,1052,1078]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This genus comprises a very heterogeneous group of species (
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFD6DFBAB5F19464A" author="Duffels" box="[749,1074,1090,1116]" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; Hayashi, M. (2006) On the identity of the cicada species Pomponia picta (Walker) (= P. fusca (Olivier )) and P. linearis (Walker) (Hemiptera, Cicadiae). Tijdschrift voor entomologie, 149, 189 - 201." type="journal article" year="2006">
Duffels and Hayashi, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFC72FBAB5F19464A" box="[1010,1074,1090,1116]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Among them, species of the 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFF17FB805A5F4694" box="[151,372,1129,1154]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFF17FB805A5F4694" box="[151,372,1129,1154]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFDD1FB8058A24695" author="Duffels" box="[593,905,1129,1155]" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; Hayashi, M. (2006) On the identity of the cicada species Pomponia picta (Walker) (= P. fusca (Olivier )) and P. linearis (Walker) (Hemiptera, Cicadiae). Tijdschrift voor entomologie, 149, 189 - 201." type="journal article" year="2006">
Duffels &amp; Hayashi (
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFCC2FB8058AA4695" box="[834,897,1129,1155]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
share the following characters: a broad pale transverse band across the postclypeus; acute lateral pygofer lobes; a trapezoidal uncus with medial incision suggesting the fusion of two short, broad lobes; and a pair of claspers, each with two spines, protruding from below the uncus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7DF542464D170CFF45FAED5E65477D" blockId="7.[151,1437,1013,1387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Four described species occur in 
<collectingCountry id="D3D5B5D2464D170CFDC5FAED59854708" box="[581,686,1284,1310]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFD39FAED5F794708" authority="Walker, 1850" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1850" box="[697,1106,1284,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFD39FAED58BE470B" box="[697,917,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia linearis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFC25FAED5F624708" author="Walker" box="[933,1097,1284,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="19" refString="Walker, F. (1850) List of the specimens of homopterous insects in the collection of the British Museum, part 1. London, pp. 1 - 260, pls. 1 - 2." type="journal article" year="1850">
Walker, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFB8AFAED5F624708" box="[1034,1097,1284,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1850.0">1850</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFBDEFAED5BFF4752" authority="Distant, 1905" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piceata">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFBDEFAED5E1C470B" box="[1118,1335,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia piceata</emphasis>
Distant, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFF17FAC35BFF4752" box="[151,212,1322,1348]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1905.0">1905</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFF60FAC2594E4752" authority="Distant, 1887" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1887" box="[224,613,1322,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lactea">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFF60FAC25A824752" box="[224,425,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia lactea</emphasis>
(Distant, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFD9DFAC359704752" box="[541,603,1322,1348]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1887.0">1887</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFD23FAC25F7A4752" authority="Distant, 1912" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1912" box="[675,1105,1322,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFD23FAC258B84752" box="[675,915,1323,1348]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia orientalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CF5388B3464D170CFC23FAC35F634752" author="Distant" box="[931,1096,1322,1348]" pageId="7" pageNumber="18" refString="Distant, W. L. (1912) New genera and species of Oriental Homoptera. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (8) 9, 459 - 471." type="journal article" year="1912">
Distant, 
<number id="1D0AE765464D170CFB89FAC35F634752" box="[1033,1096,1322,1348]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Below we present a key to species of genus 
<taxonomicName id="6CC28EC1464D170CFEE5FAB85AF6477C" box="[357,477,1361,1386]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Pomponia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99B62950464D170CFEE5FAB85AF6477C" box="[357,477,1361,1386]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Pomponia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="D3D5B5D2464D170CFDA5FAB859A0477D" box="[549,651,1361,1387]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, and describe a new species belonging to this species group.
</paragraph>
